Uganda Suspends Its Hunt for Warlord
Ugandan troops suspended their search for fugitive warlord Joseph Kony in the jungles of the Central African Republic, the Ugandan military said Wednesday, fueling fears that the country could descend into deeper disorder following the rebel overthrow of its government last month.
Uganda's military ordered army units hunting for Mr. Kony, the leader of the Lord's Resistance Army, to return to their main bases in the eastern part of the Central African Republic. That decision follows a directive issued last week by their host's...